'''Bishop Hannon High School''' was a [[Roman Catholic]] [[comprehensive school]] on Beechley Drive, [[Pentrebane]], [[Cardiff]], [[Wales]].<ref name=annual1981>{{Citation |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vEocAQAAMAAJ&dq=%22Bishop+Hannon%22+school&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22Bishop+Hannon%22+ |title=The Education Authorities Directory and Annual 1981 |publisher=The School Government Publishing Company |year=1981 |page=493 |isbn=0-900640-13-8 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.walesonline.co.uk/lifestyle/nostalgia/gallery/school-days-8604972 |title=School Days ''(Image 14 of 27)'' |work=Wales Online |date=9 February 2015 |accessdate=25 September 2018 }}</ref>

The school was built in the 1960s on a 17 acre site on the edge of what was then the new housing estates of [[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]].<ref name=egan>{{Citation|first=Josephine |last=Egan |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=BBLGZHqZs9YC&pg=PA49&lpg=PA49#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Opting Out: Catholic Schools Today |publisher=Fowler Wright Books |year=1988 |page=49 |isbn=0-85244-1312 }}</ref> Fifty pupils started in September 1965, before the school was completed in January 1966. The school was designed to take 600 pupils.<ref name=egan />

By the early 1980s the school had 670 pupils. <ref name=annual1981 />

The school was closed in 1987 and its pupils transferred to other Roman Catholic schools in the city.<ref name=egan />

