{{Use British English|date=January 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}} The '''Philosophy of Education Society of Great Britain''' was established in 1964 'to promote the development and teaching of the rigorous philosophical study of [[education]]al questions'.<ref>[http://www.ioe.ac.uk/services/1004.html Institute of Education Archives]. Accessed 14 March 2011</ref> Professor Louis Arnaud Reid was the first President. The current chair of the society is Professor Paul Standish, head of the Centre for Philosophy at the [[UCL Institute of Education]].
The Society has a regional network and its members are from both the [[United Kingdom|UK]] and overseas. Membership is open to individuals who have been or are engaged in some form of study of the [[philosophy of education]]. It also holds regular events, including an annual [[Academic conference|conference]] and publishes the ''[[Journal of Philosophy of Education]]'' and the booklet series IMPACT.<ref>[http://www.philosophy-of-education.org/ Philosophy of Education Society of Great Britain website]. Accessed 14 March 2011</ref>
